content.description: Highly recommended if looking for a fun 5.10 at cecilville. Starts on the left side of the cave and goes up some jugs to a roof. Pull on good holds through the roof for some exhilarating 5.10 moves. New leaders should be careful as there is a cruxy sequence right before the anchors.
content.location: At the flat area with the stone retaining wall, this route starts up the left side of the cave and heads right, then straight up the roof.

content.description: Another very fun route with surprisingly good rests and a variety of movement. The crux comes right off the ground with some bouldery movements, then layback and stem your way to the roof. Shake out on the monster jug then try to find the good holds over the lip, and pull to the anchors.
content.location: Just right of Tequila Sunrise, starts with a low bolt on the right side of the shallow cave.

content.description: Easy slab uip to some funky climbing over a small roof. Be careful of slack accumulation on the slab. This was originally an RB route, later rebolted.
content.location: Just barely left of the Morning Wall.

content.description:
Clip the first three bolts shared with Tequila Sunrise, but head left on the slab. Chill out on the large ledge, then set off into a slightly overhanging headwall. The crux is two bolts up, with a move that can be a little perplexing at first... think back to the rules of climbing technique, what do you do when a hold is out of reach??

After the short crux, the grade drops back down for enjoyable 5.10 to the top.

The crux bolt is sticking out of the hole almost a 1/4". Next time I'm back I'll see if it can be hammered back in and tightened, otherwise I'll replace the bolt with a fatty.
content.location: Fork left after the first three bolts shared with Tequila Sunrise, then take the first bolt line.
